The next step in the algorithm’s correctness proof is a set of lemmas on “multiplicative weights dynamics.” The specific dynamic we use to “probe” the mathematical structure and properties of symmetric bimatrix games is based on Hedge [Freund and Schapire, 1997, 1999]. In this setting, Hedge induces the following dynamic:
Ti(X) = X(i) · exp {αEi · CX}
∑n j=1X(j) exp {αEj · CX}
, i = 1, . . . , n. (1)
In this section, we give some properties of (1). We first show that X(C,CT ) is invariant under T in that T never escapes the space of mixed strategies of the game (C,CT ) in which it is invoked. Actually we also show that if T is started in the relative interior of X(C,CT ), T cannot escape X̊(C,CT ) in a finite number of steps. Then we characterize fixed points and prove some powerful lemmas. We also prove the promised “better response property” as Lemma 8 below.

