∀X ∈ X̊(C,CT ) ∀Y ∈ X(C,CT ) : RE(Y, T (X)) is a convex function of α ≥ 0.
Furthermore, unless X ∈ FX(C,CT ), RE(Y, T (X)) is a strictly convex function of α > 0.
